args:
The prince, having secured a source of food and
water, discovers Chelle collapsed on the beach.
After moving her to safety, he searches for
useful detritus from the shipwreck, and after a
string of failures, finally strikes figurative gold.
Perfect. This should be enough food and\nclean water for all of us.
You're sweating profusely! And you've\ngot a terrible fever. I need to move you\nsomeplace where you can cool off.
You've come to! What a relief.\nHow are you feeling?
I think you're just overheated.\nHere, drink this.
Looks as though you found some water.\nI'll go ahead and partake, then.\n......Ahhh.
Thank you. I should be fine in noâ€”hrk?!
What is it?! Are you hurt?
It's nothing I'd go so far as to call an\ninjury. I was attacked by a fiend while\nexploring and I twisted my ankle.
I somehow managed to escape,\nonly to collapse out in the open.\nHow tremendously shameful.
It's not as if you had gear or supplies to\nhelp you fend it off. Be kind to yourself.\nFrankly, I'm relieved it wasn't worse.
Look. You need to accept my help.\nThis is not up for debate. I need you to\nstay here and rest for the time being.
...Yes, I suppose that's for the best. \nWould you go and search the beach for\nanything that might have drifted ashore?
We might be able to raid the contents for\nsomething to help us survive this. That's\nwhat I was hoping to do earlier, at least.
Which areas have you covered so far?
I combed nearly all of the beach to the\nsoutheast of where I collapsed earlier.
Got it. I'll head to the west side and\nstart my search around there, then.
Glad to help. Be back in a bit!
The light is shining down from above here,\nand the breeze passing through feels nice.
Still, he's been gone for some time.\nSitting on the sidelines like this is\nmind-numbingly boring.
He's officially past due to return.
Honestly, can the boy not even handle a\nsimple errand? I'd better go check on him.
Darn it all. Nothing here, either.
You've covered quite a bit of ground, I see.
Chelle?! Are you sure you're good to be\nmoving around already?
You needn't fuss over me so.\nMore to the point, I'm assuming\nyou've yet to find anything?

Correct. I searched by and large out to the
west. There were steep cliffs that made it
tough to get around to the north side, so I
couldn't be especially thorough there.
Noted. The sun will be setting imminently,\nso I think it may be about time to give up\nthe search.
We can't even be certain that any of my\nluggage has washed ashore to begin with.
Searching any longer would only be a\nwaste of energy.
And energy is a resource we need to\nconserve right now. I think it wisest to\ncut our losses and try something else.
Are you really sure about that?
What are you trying to say?
You left the securing of food and water up\nto me, so that must mean you regarded\nfinding the wreckage as a top priority.
And given your mind for these sorts of\nthings, I say we hold out hope that it's\naround here somewhere and keep looking.
If whatever's inside could give us a\nfighting chance at survival, then it couldn't\nhurt to try and secure it in good time.
That may well be, but as I literally just\nexplained, we're working off a gamble at\nbest. We should call it a day on this.
And if the fiends around here end\nup finding it first and damaging it?\nWhat then?

The only place I haven't searched is to
the north. There's still some time before
sundown, so maybe we can search just a
little while longer?
If you're still not feeling fighting fit, then\nI'll cover for you there. Let's cooperate on\nthis, Chelle. As brother and sister.
Very well. If you absolutely insist,\nI relent. Buckle up, because I'm about\nto run you ragged, my little workhorse!
Er, that's not exactly what I intended...
You're the one who invoked our\nfamilial bonds, dear brother!

Now, our first order of business will be to
check if the tide has shifted. We'll run a
fine-toothed comb over every possible
place the luggage could've come ashore!
*sigh* I suppose I brought this upon\nmyself... Still, it's an improvement.
That's enough mumbling from you. We're\nworking against the clock here, remember?
The north beach, shortly after the prince\nwalked face-first into indentured servitude...
*huff* *huff* Looks like I managed to\nshake off the fiends.
Chelle wasn't kidding about running\nme ragged, though.
Good work, dear brother. You made a great\ndecoy. Just as I'd expect from my horsey!

Um, let's leave that nickname in our
childhood memories where it belongs.
Were you able to collect the luggage
that washed ashore?
Yes. I can't believe those uppity fiends had\nthe nerve to steal it!
Right? If we had come any later,\nthey would've probably ruined it.
I'm glad I convinced you to keep searching.
So, was there anything in the luggage that\nwe could use?
Indeed. Namely, preserved food, blankets,\nflint, and even a hunting knife.
Wow. That couldn't be more perfect. But\nwhy did you pack that in the first place?
Oh, just in case something of this nature\nhappened. A proper lady always makes\ndoubly sure she is ready for any situation.
And in that sense, the most important\nthing in the bag...was THIS!
What in the world is that?
Eee hee hee! This, Brother dearest, is our\nbest hope of getting home alive!
